@startuml
autonumber

Actor User
Participant "Frontend (React)" as Frontend
Participant "Web API (Controllers)" as API
Participant "Business Logic (Services)" as BusinessLogic
Database "PostgreSQL" as Database

User -> Frontend: Opens Dashboard
Frontend -> API: GET /dashboard/data (Auth Token)

alt Successful Data Fetch
    API -> BusinessLogic: Request dashboard data (e.g., recent transactions, account summaries)
    BusinessLogic -> Database: Query various tables (e.g., Transactions, Accounts, Categories)
    Database --> BusinessLogic: Raw dashboard data
    BusinessLogic --> API: Processed dashboard data
    API --> Frontend: Dashboard data (JSON)
    Frontend --> User: Displays Dashboard with loaded data
else Data Fetch Failed
    API --> Frontend: Error message (e.g., Server error, No data)
    Frontend --> User: Displays Error message or empty state
end

@enduml